1
00:00:06,205 --> 00:00:10,035
We know that devotees
at the time of initiation

2
00:00:10,035 --> 00:00:12,775
they very much like to hear
the meaning of their name.

3
00:00:12,995 --> 00:00:16,975
[What’s in a Name?]

4
00:00:17,335 --> 00:00:21,115
They are very eager 
to hear that.

5
00:00:21,305 --> 00:00:23,819
And even Guru Mahārāj
asked Saraswatī T􏰅hākur.

6
00:00:23,819 --> 00:00:26,867
His name was
Ramendra Chandra Bhaṭṭācārya;

7
00:00:26,963 --> 00:00:30,991
he got initiated, and his name became
Ramendra Sundar.

8
00:00:31,191 --> 00:00:33,097
And he said, 
“How shall I …

9
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:37,868
What that Ramendra 
here means?”

10
00:00:38,088 --> 00:00:41,848
And Saraswatī Т̣hākur
began to explain,

11
00:00:41,848 --> 00:00:46,358
“Rāma, Hare Rāma,
that Rāma

12
00:00:46,358 --> 00:00:49,826
is not Rāmacandra
or Balarāma, but

13
00:00:49,836 --> 00:00:53,106
Rādhā–Raman, 
Raman–Rādhā—

14
00:00:55,577 --> 00:00:58,397
the lover of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī,

15
00:00:58,397 --> 00:01:00,106
when He is giving joy
and happiness

16
00:01:00,106 --> 00:01:03,246
to Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī
in divine pastimes.”

17
00:01:03,246 --> 00:01:04,356
And Guru Mahārāj said,

18
00:01:04,356 --> 00:01:07,116
“And that sound
is still ringing in my ear.”

19
00:01:07,116 --> 00:01:09,146
So even he asked.

20
00:01:11,506 --> 00:01:15,716
But Śrīla Gurudev, 
he didn’t like

21
00:01:15,716 --> 00:01:18,716
devotees to ask.
[Laughing]

22
00:01:18,716 --> 00:01:21,606
It’s just one 
of those things. [Laughing]

23
00:01:22,139 --> 00:01:24,179
And sometimes 
he would say

24
00:01:24,179 --> 00:01:27,179
if they say,
“What is my name?”,

25
00:01:27,179 --> 00:01:28,010
He’d say,

26
00:01:28,010 --> 00:01:30,620
“What was your 
Christian name?

27
00:01:31,310 --> 00:01:34,310
Do you know 
what that means?”

28
00:01:34,310 --> 00:01:36,974
So once this boy
from Australia,

29
00:01:36,974 --> 00:01:40,829
who is an excellent craftsman,
he made all those tables

30
00:01:40,829 --> 00:01:44,475
in the Theistic Media Center 
at the Sevak Bhavan;

31
00:01:44,475 --> 00:01:48,940
Madhuranan, he was sitting
on the Veranda once,

32
00:01:48,940 --> 00:01:51,210
and,
[in a deep voice]

33
00:01:51,210 --> 00:01:56,750
“Śrīla Govinda Mahārāj,
Śrīla Gurudev?”

34
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:58,590
Gurudev, “Yes?”

35
00:01:58,595 --> 00:02:00,525
[in a deep voice]
“Can I ask you a question?”

36
00:02:00,525 --> 00:02:01,234
[Laughing]

37
00:02:01,234 --> 00:02:02,814
Gurudev goes like, “Yes”,
and he goes,

38
00:02:02,829 --> 00:02:05,609
“What does 
Hare Kṛṣṇa mean?”

39
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:09,123
Gurudev put
his newspaper down

40
00:02:11,235 --> 00:02:14,855
and said, 
“What was your name before?”

41
00:02:14,855 --> 00:02:17,055
He said,
[sternly] “Matthew.”

42
00:02:17,715 --> 00:02:19,558
Gurudev,
“What does Matthew mean?”

43
00:02:19,558 --> 00:02:21,762
[sternly], 
“Messenger of God.”

44
00:02:23,508 --> 00:02:26,268
Gurudev said,
“Oh, alright,”

45
00:02:26,268 --> 00:02:28,588
and folded
the newspaper and …

46
00:02:28,588 --> 00:02:30,908
[Laughing]

47
00:02:30,908 --> 00:02:32,788
Because usually he’d say,
“What does that mean?”

48
00:02:32,788 --> 00:02:35,948
and they don’t know 
what their name means.

49
00:02:35,948 --> 00:02:37,931
But he said, [sternly]
“Messenger of God.”

50
00:02:37,931 --> 00:02:40,831
[Laughing]

51
00:02:40,831 --> 00:02:43,634
Then he said, 
“Alright …”

52
00:02:45,744 --> 00:02:50,378
And he started explaining 
something about mahā-mantra.

53
00:02:51,507 --> 00:02:58,337
And I should say, on one level
we are forbidden

54
00:02:58,653 --> 00:03:02,653
from going into the detailed 
explanations of that,

55
00:03:02,653 --> 00:03:05,723
and we can say
we don’t even know them.

56
00:03:06,613 --> 00:03:09,613
But this type of analysis …

57
00:03:09,613 --> 00:03:11,889
But what you have there,

58
00:03:12,381 --> 00:03:15,501
what you’ve read there,

59
00:03:15,654 --> 00:03:18,984
that sort of general indication

60
00:03:19,737 --> 00:03:23,527
is what’s given to us.

61
00:03:23,914 --> 00:03:28,234
So sometimes 
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj,

62
00:03:28,239 --> 00:03:29,999
Śrīla Swāmī Mahārāj 
as well

63
00:03:31,695 --> 00:03:36,435
would point out, 
‘Hare’ is in the vocative case,

64
00:03:36,657 --> 00:03:40,507
which means,
in Guru Maharāj’s words,

65
00:03:40,547 --> 00:03:44,127
“No plea 
is to be attached to this.”

66
00:03:44,244 --> 00:03:47,474
We are not chanting
for something.

67
00:03:49,694 --> 00:03:51,329
People have 
that idea sometimes,

68
00:03:51,329 --> 00:03:55,859
that you will chant the mantra 
to get something.

69
00:03:56,629 --> 00:04:00,189
So that was 
Guru Mahārāj’s expression,

70
00:04:00,189 --> 00:04:03,189
“No plea is to be attached.

71
00:04:03,189 --> 00:04:11,159
Just invoking ‘Hare—
Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī and Kṛṣṇa.’”

72
00:04:12,388 --> 00:04:16,458
But … And Śrīla Prabhupād
(Swāmī Mahārāj)

73
00:04:16,502 --> 00:04:20,032
when he gave 
a general explanation too,

74
00:04:20,032 --> 00:04:26,392
he said, “It’s like a prayer 
to be engaged in service.”

75
00:04:30,404 --> 00:04:35,864
So all of these things:
service, seva,

76
00:04:35,864 --> 00:04:41,022
dās, dāsī, 
Kṛṣṇa dās, Rādhā dāsī—

77
00:04:41,033 --> 00:04:46,143
they have some general meaning
and some more specific meaning.

78
00:04:46,857 --> 00:04:48,607
And Śrīla Guru Mahārāj 
will say,

79
00:04:48,607 --> 00:04:52,487
“According to the inner awakenment

80
00:04:53,438 --> 00:04:57,168
of the devotee,
the aspiring servitor,

81
00:05:00,431 --> 00:05:05,623
meaning is attached or revealed,
or things reveal

82
00:05:05,623 --> 00:05:08,443
deeper sorts of meaning.”

83
00:05:09,301 --> 00:05:11,359
But one thing
Guru Mahārāj said,

84
00:05:11,359 --> 00:05:14,069
that’s really astonishing,

85
00:05:14,071 --> 00:05:18,891
he said, “By chanting 
Hare Kṛṣṇa mahā-mantra”,

86
00:05:18,891 --> 00:05:21,012
he said, 
“one day you will find

87
00:05:21,012 --> 00:05:25,162
that you are in the harem
of Kṛṣṇa.”

